social_posts.post_text: confirmation I was born in the wrong era ⏳
See ya never, 2022. You quite literally kicked my ass.

My heart is still so full from this weekend. Campbell River diving is outstanding. We were beyond lucky on our last dive to spend it drifting along a wall listening to the conversation between two humpback whales. I could’ve stayed down there forever 🐋 I am so grateful to have been surrounded by such inspiring and amazing divers all weekend. Heart is happy and full 🦭🦀

Join me in the waters of British Columbia 🤿🪸 

Divers of IG, do you have a song that plays in your head while diving? Comment them below! Mine is Goodbye Yellow Brick Road 🎼
75 days later and WE MADE ITTTTT 🤩 75 soft was the challenge of a lifetime and I would do it again in a heartbeat.
Happy birthday to my best friend, my adventure buddy, the Hufflepuff to my Gryffindor ❤️ I’m endlessly proud of you, I can’t wait to see what the next year brings 🤍🐏🎂

I can’t BELIEVE that I just did a half marathon. I’m so beyond proud of myself. Four months of hard work, strength, and serious happiness training 🥹 running brings me such joy and empowerment. Today is a great day 🤍
I’m an official smartypants 👩🏽‍🎓🎓 my heart is so full of love and joy! Big thank you to all the family, friends and professors that got me here 💙 I can’t wait for what comes next!
the best day exploring nature with my love 💚
Ferdi’s first trip to see the mouse 🐭🤍

LACMA was unreal but I cannot believe I got the chance to see the ORIGINAL portrait of Sengbe Pieh (Joseph Cinqué). What a beautiful surprise 🥹

The Black Atlantic exhibit was absolutely beautiful and breathtaking. It’s only at LACMA for another week or so - you must go!!!!!
we part like the Red Sea when the queen comes to Vancouver 🐝

life is not a waste of time and time is not a waste of life so let’s stop wasting time, get wasted and have the time of our lives 🌍 

this weekend gave EVERYTHINGGGG, I will always pay all the money to see Mr. Worldwide 🙏🏽♥️

2023 was a year of healing and happiness. I feel so lucky. I met the love of my life, ran my first half marathon, graduated with my first degree, and created so many beautiful memories ♥️ I’m ready to see what 2024 brings for me.
